result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin C. Jeter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Justin C. Jeter in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Justin C. Jeter in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CM149 and 14CF128 @ 9:40 a.m. Parties have received revocation packet. No additions or corrections. State joins Dept's recommendation for 6 months jail, gives arguments. Atty Schuster in agreement with Dept., gives arguments. 14CF128 - 104 days credit. 15CM149 - 55 days credit. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Court approves joint recommendation. 14CF128 ct 1 - 6 months jail, credit for 104 days served, huber as allowed for work or child care, ct 2 - 6 months jail, credit for 104 days, huber, concurrent, ct 3 - 6 months jail, concurrent, credit for 104 days served, huber. 15CM149 ct 1 - 6 months jail, concurrent to 14CF128, credit for 55 days served, huber. No outstanding court obligations. Postconviction rights.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on June 22, 2016 at 10:30 am.

Defendant Justin C. Jeter in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 10:27 a.m. Agreement stated - State has complied with VWNR. Def will plead to charge, withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA and follow through, court costs. Atty Schuster agrees, asks bond be returned to poster. Def agrees. Court reviews plea quest. Guilty plea. Constitutional rights, elements and possible penalties reviewed. Atty Schuster satisfied. Court finds Def understands and plea freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts plea and finds Def guilty. Def admits prior convictions. Statement by Atty Schuster. Statement by Def. Court will follow agreement. Withheld prison sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA and follow through, court costs. Return bond to poster.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. No credit if revoked. DNA sample and surcharge. DNA colloquy. Postconviction rights.

Defendant Justin C. Jeter in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint received, reviewed and waive reading.  Not guilty plea entered.Court accepts plea.  Bond will continue  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 25, 2015 at 10:15 am.

Defendant Justin C. Jeter in court, via video, in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def has copy of complaint.  Court reads charge with possible penalties.  Def advised of right to an atty.   Def wishes to contact an atty.  Bond has been set.  Def is on probation hold.  Bond will continue with condition.
